            dedication_title: "Dedication",
            dedication_body_md: "**Dedicated to Ricardo M. F., my beloved brother.**\n\nI took a sabbatical year to devote myself to literary creation.  \nI saved money, prepared myself, and the year arrived. In March, objects began to tremble and everything broke: the world was facing a pandemic. That was the year 2020. I lost relatives, I suffered, but I did not stop. I wrote at funerals, locked down with sick people at home, fighting the world, until I lost my brother.\n\nThe **‚ÄúK‚Äù** you see as the image of this project is a drawing by him, based on a nickname he loved to be called: **Fluck**. After his death, I found a letter of reconciliation from 2017, when he came to visit me in Rio de Janeiro and hid it inside my favourite book. He knew that one day I would open that book again. I tattooed his signature from that letter, and while writing the code I realised I needed something of my own, a personal gesture ‚Äî and from my tattoo the **eskrev** project logo was born.\n\nI present to you the philosophy of this project. It was a time before artificial intelligence. The **Fio do Verso** is raw. I did not edit a single word. It is true. It is my 2020 transformed into literary text, for you.\n\nIf it serves as inspiration, pretend you are in 2001, in 1982, and write freely. Even if a meteor falls, even if someone bares their sharp teeth against your dreams, this site will be on your laptop: ready, complete, offline, in four languages. **This is my contribution. We will be prepared.**\n\n**Fluck, wherever you are, thank you. I love you.**",
            dedication_fio_note_md: "The **366 complete texts** of **Fio do Verso ‚Äî 2020**, in Portuguese (pt-BR), are available on this site via **Reader Mode**, accessible through the **library icon**.\n\n**Nothing is sent. Nothing is tracked. Everything stays local.**",
